1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.333
Knox cloud services 26.06 release highlights.

2
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:06.333
Here's what's new in the Knox Admin Portal.

3
00:00:06.333 --> 00:00:08.666
A new Security Dashboard.

4
00:00:08.666 --> 00:00:12.666
A new Security dashboard lets you see which devices in your fleet 

5
00:00:12.666 --> 00:00:16.666
require the latest security patches, and which ones are at, or nearing their end-of-life

6
00:00:16.666 --> 00:00:19.066
dates for OS and security patch support.

7
00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:23.262
You can access this new dashboard by clicking the new Device lifecycle

8
00:00:23.262 --> 00:00:26.407
summary tile on the main Knox Admin Portal Dashboard, 

9
00:00:26.407 --> 00:00:29.732
or by clicking the Security link in the left navigation pane. 

10
00:00:29.733 --> 00:00:33.733
Additionally, you can enable email notifications to receive snapshots 

11
00:00:33.733 --> 00:00:37.733
of your fleets security status, or get alerts whenever devices approach 

12
00:00:37.733 --> 00:00:39.333
their security end-of-life dates 

13
00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:42.400
or when devices have their security patch cadence changed. 

14
00:00:43.266 --> 00:00:46.332
Enroll devices without requiring a factory reset.

15
00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:49.389
If you have devices already active and in use, 

16
00:00:49.389 --> 00:00:53.099
you can now enroll them in Knox E-FOTA and Knox Asset Intelligence 

17
00:00:53.100 --> 00:00:55.133
without requiring a factory reset.

18
00:00:55.700 --> 00:00:58.445
This allows you to easily try these additional services 

19
00:00:58.445 --> 00:01:00.565
with minimal disruptions to your business.

20
00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:04.346
Perform additional actions from the Devices page.

21
00:01:04.346 --> 00:01:08.682
This release simplifies device management by consolidating cross-service actions 

22
00:01:08.683 --> 00:01:14.921
for Knox Mobile Enrollment, Knox E-FOTA, Knox Asset Intelligence, and Knox Configure

23
00:01:14.921 --> 00:01:18.526
into a single Actions drop-down menu on the Devices page.

24
00:01:18.527 --> 00:01:22.159
For example, if you previously wanted to perform device actions

25
00:01:22.159 --> 00:01:25.791
like requesting a diagnostic log or forcing a client refresh,

26
00:01:25.792 --> 00:01:29.933
you had to do this in Knox Asset Intelligence and Knox E-FOTA separately.

27
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:34.675
With this release, you can now perform device-related tasks more efficiently 

28
00:01:34.675 --> 00:01:37.245
without switching between multiple service consoles, 

29
00:01:37.246 --> 00:01:40.899
reducing administrative overhead and minimizing the risk of errors.

30
00:01:42.133 --> 00:01:46.133
To learn more about the features in this release, or to get additional help at any time, 

31
00:01:46.133 --> 00:01:49.433
see our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

32
00:01:49.700 --> 00:01:50.866
Thanks for watching!

